You can make these books on your phone or computer whereas you can’t with the subscription books. This is nice when you are editing comments. (You can’t enlarge in preview mode and the printing is so small. It’s nice to be able to edit on the computer.)

Review Title: System Glitches Made This Book More Difficult Than Most
Review Text: I have had positive experiences overall with chatbooks and have now made 9 year-long books with them. I am a creature of habit and had a good system for creating my books, so unfortunately lots of changes being rolled out in a short time made for a frustrating working experience for my most recent book. Lots of the bugs were not worked out, which made an already time consuming project much longer, and I was demotivated to work on them. Thankfully, some of the bugs were fixed towards the end of my project.  What I’m struggling with the most now is changes that affect the consistency of the books. Like shortening the character count for the title on the spine. This throws off the pattern of consistency I had hoped to have across volumes of books year to year. Same with the automatic font size increase once you exceed a certain page count. I did feel like support was very responsive to my questions. However, my last support inquiry was answered by a bot, which was disappointing. Overall, I used to enjoy the process of making these books more prior to many of the changes, which feel more restrictive. At least when working from a desktop (which is all I use). It seems as though the changes may better cater to those working from the app on the phone.

Review Text: My grandson loves looking at photos and I thought it would be cute to give him his own book to have.  I expected this small book to be something I could give to a toddler and not worry about the book getting destroyed.  The first thing that struck me was the sharp corners on the cover.  I thought a softcover book would actually be soft all over, including the corners.  While the cover itself is, the corners are not. The pictures came out okay but I am used to the 10 x 10 books I typically order.  The pictures are clearer in the large book.  The issue may be due to making collages on the pages of the small book.  If I were to order another small book I think it would be better to limit the photos to 1 or 2 per page for better clarity.  It would be nice to have an option to order rounded corners on the cover and pages.
